There is no required textbook for this course, but the following books are
recommended reference texts. Prof. Ian Hutchinson's 2003 lecture_notes are also
included on this page.
***** References *****
**** General ****
Elementary:
[Amazon_logo] Chen, F. F. Introduction to Plasma Physics. 2nd ed. New York, NY:
Springer, 1984. ISBN: 9780306413322.
See also:
[Amazon_logo] Shohet, J. L. The Plasma State. San Diego, CA: Academic Press
Inc., 1971. ISBN: 9780126405507.
[Amazon_logo] Tanenbaum, B. S. Plasma Physics. New York, NY: McGraw-Hill, 1967.
ISBN: 9780070628120.
Intermediate:
[Amazon_logo] Hazeltine, R. D., and F. L. Waelbroeck. The Framework of Plasma
Physics. Boulder, CO: Westview Press, 2004. ISBN: 9780813342139.
[Amazon_logo] Goldston, R. J., and P. H. Rutherford. Introduction to Plasma
Physics. Philadelphia, PA: IOP Publishing, 1995. ISBN: 9780750301831.
See also:
[Amazon_logo] Clemmow, P. C., and J. P. Dougherty. Electrodynamics of Particles
and Plasmas. New York, NY: Perseus Books, 1989. ISBN: 9780201515008.
[Amazon_logo] Spitzer, Lyman, Jr. Physics of Fully Ionized Gases. 2nd ed.
Hoboken, NJ: Wiley, 1962.
[Amazon_logo] Schmidt, G. Physics of High Temperature Plasmas. 2nd ed. San
Diego, CA: Academic Press, 1979. ISBN: 9780126266603. (Recommended for theory
of particle orbits.)
[Amazon_logo] Boyd, T. J. M., and J. J. Sanderson. Plasma Dynamics. New York,
NY: Barnes and Noble, 1969. (Recommended for the statistical mechanics
description of plasmas.)
[Amazon_logo] Dendy, R., ed. Plasma Physics. Cambridge, UK: Cambridge
University Press, 1995. ISBN: 9780521484527. (Recommended for specific chapters
on space and plasmas and on industrial plasmas.)
Advanced:
[Amazon_logo] Krall, N. A., and A. W. Trivelpiece. Principles of Plasma
Physics. Berkeley, CA: San Francisco Press, 1986. ISBN: 9780911302585.
See also:
[Amazon_logo] Ichimaru, S. Principles of Plasma Physics - A Statistical
Approach. Boston, MA: Addison Wesley Publishing Company, 1973. ISBN:
9780805387520.
**** MHD ****
[Amazon_logo] J. P. Freidberg. Ideal Magnetohydrodynamics. New York, NY:
Springer, 1987. ISBN: 9780306425127.
**** Plasma Waves ****
[Amazon_logo] Stix, T. H. Waves in Plasmas. New York, NY: Springer, 1992. ISBN:
9780883188590.
**** Plasma Diagnostics ****
[Amazon_logo] Huddlestone, R. H., and S. L. Leonard. Plasma Diagnostic
Techniques. San Diego, CA: Academic Press, 1965.
[Amazon_logo] Hutchinson, I. H. Principles of Plasma Diagnostics. Cambridge,
UK: Cambridge University Press, 2005. ISBN: 9780521675741.
**** Magnetic Confinement Fusion ****
[Amazon_logo] Rose, D. J., and M. Clark, Jr. Plasmas_and_Controlled_Fusion.
Cambridge, MA: MIT Press, 1961. ISBN: 9780262180061.
[Amazon_logo] Miyamoto, K. Plasma_Physics_for_Nuclear_Fusion. Cambridge, MA:
MIT Press, 1989. ISBN: 9780262631174.
[Amazon_logo] Wesson, J. Tokamaks. 3rd ed. Oxford, UK: Oxford University Press,
2004. ISBN: 9780198509226.
**** Plasma Astrophysics ****
[Amazon_logo] Tajima, T., and K. Shibata. Plasma Astrophysics. Boulder, CO:
Westview Press, 2002. ISBN: 9780813339962.
Lecture Notes
